Package org.rapidcontext.util

Provides utility functions for common Java patterns.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HttpUtil
    A set of utility methods and constants for the HTTP protocol.
    HttpUtil.HEADER
    A number of standard HTTP headers as defined in RFC1945 (HTTP/1.0), RFC2616 (HTTP/1.1), and RFC4918 (WebDAV).
    HttpUtil.METHOD
    The HTTP methods as defined in RFC1945 (HTTP/1.0), RFC2616 (HTTP/1.1), RFC5789 (PATCH) and RFC4918 (WebDAV).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling native arrays.
    BinaryUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling binary data.
    ClasspathUtil
    A set of utility methods for working with the classpath and class loaders.
    DateUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling date and time objects.
    FileUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling files.
    HttpUtil.Helper
    Some static utility methods for HTTP.
    HttpUtil.STATUS
    The HTTP status codes as defined in RFC1945 (HTTP/1.0), RFC2616 (HTTP/1.1), and RFC4918 (WebDAV).
    StringUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling strings and characters.
    ZipUtil
    A set of utility methods for handling ZIP files.

Package org.rapidcontext.util Description

Provides utility functions for common Java patterns. Note that this package strives to avoid duplicating utility code available elsewhere (without including unreasonably large JAR files).
